    "5 Advantages and disadvantages of using thiazine dyes as photosensitizers",
    "Thiazine dyes are a class of synthetic organic dyes that contain a thiazine ring structure as shown in Figure 1.",
    "These dyes are commonly used in various industrial applications, including textile dyeing, paper colouring, and as biological stains.",
    "The toxicity of thiazine dyes in water can vary depending on the specific dye and its chemical composition (Handbook of Green and Sustainable Nanotechnology, 2023; Rani and Shanker, 2023; Abilaji et al., 2023).",
